To get this all to install

Packages required:
 * exim4-daemon-heavy
 * spamassassin
 * dovecot-imapd, dovecot-pop3d
 * clamav-daemon
 * ruby1.8 (for scan-rewrites.rb)
 * perl
 * make
 * libsys-syslog-perl (for checlpassword.pl)

Once those are installed, do the following
 2) adduser clamav Debian-exim 
 3) change ENABLED=0 to ENABLED=1 in /etc/defaults/spamassassin
 4a) copy exim4/Makefile to /etc/exim4
 4b) copy the whole of exim4/bytemark-vhost.d to /etc/exim4
 4c) change to /etc/exim4 and run make
 5) copy exim4/rewrite-scan.rb to /usr/local/sbin
 6) copy exim4/rewrite-scan.cron to /etc/cron.d/rewrite-scan
 7) touch /etc/exim4/rewrites as user Debian-exim (or chown it)
 8) copy dovecot/dovecot.conf to /etc/dovecot
 9) copy dovecot/checkpassword.pl to /usr/local/sbin

I *think* that is it.

### So commands are as follows
sudo apt-get install exim4-daemon-heavy spamassassin dovecot-imapd dovecot-pop3d clamav-daemon ruby perl libsys-syslog-perl
adduser clamav Debian-exim
sed -i -e 's/^\(ENABLED=\)0/\11/' /etc/default/spamassassin 
cp -R exim4/bytemark-vhost.d /etc/exim4
cp exim4/Makefile /etc/exim4
cd /etc/exim4 && make
cp exim4/exim_rewrite_scan.rb /usr/local/sbin
cp exim4/exim_rewrite_scan.cron /etc/cron.d/exim_rewrite_scan
touch /etc/exim4/rewrites
chown Debian-exim /etc/exim4/rewrites
cp dovecot/dovecot.conf /etc/dovecot/dovecot.conf
cp dovcot/checkpassword.pl /usr/local/sbin

# Now (re)start the services
/etc/init.d/spamassassin start
/etc/init.d/clamav-daemon restart
/etc/init.d/exim4 restart
/etc/init.d/dovecot restart

